ck\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mrq1665702761335.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mrq1665702761335.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mrq1665702761335.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mrq1665702761335\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">endtry\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__endtry_217113\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines the end of a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try...endtry</span> block used to handle exceptions.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__topic_d71516e1_d71517e1_d71518e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104mrq1665702761335_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__d6673e17\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">try\n    &lt;ProcScript that may throw an exception&gt;\n{catch} {ErrorNumber1 {, ErrorNumberN}}\n    &lt;Procscript that handles the error &gt;}\n{rethrow}\n{finally}\n     &lt;ProcScript that will always execute, regardless of whether an error occurred or not&gt;\nendtry</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__topic_d47037e1_d47038e1_d47039e1_d47040e1_d47041e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537910e66\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__topic_d47042e1_d47043e1_d47044e1_d47045e1_d47046e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d537910e75\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__p_d71531e1_d71532e1_d71533e1\">For each <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try</span> declaration, it is\n        possible to have multiple <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">catch</span> statements to test for specific errors,\n        as well as a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rethrow</span> statement, and/or a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">finally</span>\n        block. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">endtry</span> command must come at the end.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mrq1665702761335__p_d71534e1_d71535e1_d71536e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sal1665702761072.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sal1665702761072.html\" title=\"A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception.\">try</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rue1665702683651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Exception Handling</a><p>Exceptions are abnormal runtime events that may occur after executing a software instruction. Uncaught exceptions cause code execution to stop and the application to exit with a description of the error and where it occurred.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sal1665702761072.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>try</a><p>A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lhc1665702761265.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>catch</a><p>In a try...endtry block, introduces the code to catch and handle exceptions.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nab1665702580017.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>finally</a><p>Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzp1665702760995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>rethrow</a><p>Rethrows an exception that was caught in a catch block.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614658\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614658\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "endtry Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 endtry Defines the end of a try...endtry block used to handle exceptions. Explain this code try <ProcScript that may throw an exception> {catch} {ErrorNumber1 {, ErrorNumberN}} <Procscript that handles the error >} {rethrow} {finally} <ProcScript that will always execute, regardless of whether an error occurred or not> endtry Copy Use Allowed in all component types. Description For each try declaration, it is possible to have multiple catch statements to test for specific errors, as well as a rethrow statement, and/or a finally block. The endtry command must come at the end. For more information, see try . Related Links Exception Handling Exceptions are abnormal runtime events that may occur after executing a software instruction. Uncaught exceptions cause code execution to stop and the application to exit with a description of the error and where it occurred. try A try block specifies a ProcScript instruction, or set of instructions, that could raise an exception. catch In a try...endtry block, introduces the code to catch and handle exceptions. finally Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not. rethrow Rethrows an exception that was caught in a catch block. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}